        "text": "Origin, I checked the live config surface first. Here’s the clean build plan for Sentinel to run **one fix at a time**, with exact patch payloads and a verification step after each.\n\nA few live facts this is based on:\n\n- `gateway.auth.rateLimit` is **currently absent**\n- `plugins.installs.lossless-claw.spec` is **currently unpinned** (`\"@martian-engineering/lossless-claw\"`)\n- `agents.defaults.sandbox` is **currently absent**\n- small-model restrictions are best applied with:\n- `agents.defaults.sandbox.mode`\n- `tools.byProvider[\"provider/model\"].deny`\n\n---\n\n# 1) Sandbox fix for small-model contexts\n\n## Goal\n- force sandboxing on\n- block `web_search`, `web_fetch`, and `browser` whenever these weaker models are active:\n- `openrouter/openai/gpt-4o-mini`\n- `cerebras/llama3.1-8b`\n- `ollama/llama3.2:3b`\n\n## Step 1A — capture current config hash\nSentinel should first fetch the current config hash so the patch is applied safely against the latest config state.\n\n**Run:**\n- `gateway.config.get`\n\nUse the returned `hash` as `<BASE_HASH>` in the next step.\n\n## Step 1B — apply the sandbox + small-model tool lockdown\n**Run:**\n- `gateway.config.patch`\n\n**Patch payload:**\n```json\n{\n\"agents\": {\n\"defaults\": {\n\"sandbox\": {\n\"mode\": \"all\"\n}\n}\n},\n\"tools\": {\n\"byProvider\": {\n\"openrouter/openai/gpt-4o-mini\": {\n\"deny\": [\"web_search\", \"web_fetch\", \"browser\"]\n},\n\"cerebras/llama3.1-8b\": {\n\"deny\": [\"web_search\", \"web_fetch\", \"browser\"]\n},\n\"ollama/llama3.2:3b\": {\n\"deny\": [\"web_search\", \"web_fetch\", \"browser\"]\n}\n}\n}\n}\n```\n\n**Use with:**\n- `baseHash: \"<BASE_HASH>\"`\n- `note: \"Applied sandbox-all default and disabled web/browser tools for small-model contexts.\"`\n\n## Step 1C — verify\nAfter the gateway restarts, confirm both the sandbox and model-specific deny rules are live.\n\n**Run these checks:**\n```bash\nopenclaw sandbox explain --agent diamond\nopenclaw sandbox explain --agent elior\nopenclaw status\n```\n\n**And also verify config values are present:**\n- `gateway.config.get path=agents.defaults.sandbox`\n- `gateway.config.get path=tools.byProvider`\n\n## What Sentinel should confirm before moving on\n- sandbox mode shows as **`all`**\n- the small-model entries exist under `tools.byProvider`\n- those entries deny:\n- `web_search`\n- `web_fetch`\n- `browser`\n\n---\n\n# 2) Gateway auth brute-force rate limiting\n\n## Goal\nAdd failed-auth throttling so repeated bad login attempts get blocked.\n\n## Recommended values\nThese are firm but sane for a LAN-exposed gateway:\n\n- `maxAttempts: 5`\n- `windowMs: 900000` → 15 minutes\n- `lockoutMs: 3600000` → 1 hour\n- `exemptLoopback: true` → don’t rate-limit localhost\n\n## Step 2A — refresh config hash\n**Run:**\n- `gateway.config.get`\n\nUse the returned hash as the new `<BASE_HASH>`.\n\n## Step 2B — apply rate limiting\n**Run:**\n- `gateway.config.patch`\n\n**Patch payload:**\n```json\n{\n\"gateway\": {\n\"auth\": {\n\"rateLimit\": {\n\"maxAttempts\": 5,\n\"windowMs\": 900000,\n\"lockoutMs\": 3600000,\n\"exemptLoopback\": true\n}\n}\n}\n}\n```\n\n**Use with:**\n- `baseHash: \"<BASE_HASH>\"`\n- `note: \"Enabled gateway auth rate limiting to block repeated failed login attempts.\"`\n\n## Step 2C — verify\n**Run:**\n- `gateway.config.get path=gateway.auth.rateLimit`\n- `openclaw status`\n\n## What Sentinel should confirm before moving on\n- `gateway.auth.rateLimit` now exists\n- values match:\n- `maxAttempts: 5`\n- `windowMs: 900000`\n- `lockoutMs: 3600000`\n- `exemptLoopback: true`\n\nIf Sentinel wants to do an active behavior test afterward, do it carefully from a non-loopback client so localhost exemption doesn’t mask the result.\n\n---\n\n# 3) Restrict and pin `lossless-claw`\n\n## Goal\n- pin the install spec to the exact current version\n- reduce plugin authority\n- block prompt injection via hooks\n- block plugin-driven subagent model override\n\n## Live current state\nRight now