Short execution order for Sentinel\n\n## Fix 1\n1. `gateway.config.get`\n2. apply sandbox/tool patch\n3. verify with `openclaw sandbox explain --agent ...`\n\n## Fix 2\n1. `gateway.config.get`\n2. apply auth rate-limit patch\n3. verify `gateway.auth.rateLimit`\n\n## Fix 3\n1. `gateway.config.get`\n2. apply plugin restriction/pin patch\n3. verify plugin policy + pinned spec\n\n---\n\n# Important note\nThe **sandbox fix is global** (`agents.defaults.sandbox.mode = \"all\"`), because the current config surface exposes **model-specific tool policy** cleanly, but not **model-specific sandbox mode**. This is the safest exact fix that Sentinel can apply without risky array surgery on `agents.list`.\n\nIf you want, I can do the next pass and turn this into a **Sentinel-ready runbook** with the exact `gateway.config.patch(...)` call format spelled out line-by-line, including the expected success output after each step.",
